summary: I believe Dan and Phil when they say that Phil is fine and he was just exhausted. If we didn’t know that and if something VERY...
body:
I believe Dan and Phil when they say that Phil is fine and he was just exhausted. If we didn’t know that and if something VERY SERIOUS was going on, I wouldn’t have made any jokes. However there is absolutely no need to freak out whether or not Phil is okay. He fainted, went to the hospital, was released after some testing, and is now fine. We’ve gotten a few confirmations of that.

Just the fact that they were being goofy is enough to show that we have NO NEED to be freaked out about ANYTHING. If something serious was going on, they most likely wouldn’t have shared it with us. So to everyone making a big deal out of nothing; stop. Just breathe. Not everything has to be serious and treated as a PSA.

summary:
BREAKING NEWS
Daniel Howell, British YouTuber and co-leader of a cult branded "The Phandom", breaks thousands of furries' hearts...
body:
BREAKING NEWS

Daniel Howell, British YouTuber and co-leader of a cult branded “The Phandom”, breaks thousands of furries’ hearts with his departure from the furry community. On the 25th of October, Howell rebranded his account on the social media platform Twitter after entering into the furry community, taking on the fursona ‘Danyiff Howl’ the slothbear/fox. A week later, following the confusion of many fans, Howell released a statement on his Twitter that read: “i don’t know why everyone is expecting me to change my twitter 'back to normal’ this is my truth i’m really disappointed that you aren’t supporting me”. Could this be the reason that Howell has left the furry community?

Howell’s flatmate Philip (AmazingPhil) Lester, the other co-leader of “The Phandom”, has stayed silent through these events. Will Lester release a statement soon or will he remain in the shadows?

@danielhowell @amazingphil

(y'all two better give this some recognition i spent like twenty minutes or more on this)
